          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The current thread’s run loop runs in the default mode (see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/cfrunloop/default_run_loop_mode",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") until the run loop is stopped with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1541796-cfrunloopstop",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or all the sources and timers are removed from the default run loop mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Run loops can be run recursively. You can call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1542011-cfrunlooprun",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " from within any run loop callout and create nested run loop activations on the current thread’s call stack.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
